.TH "uart_remove_one_port" 9 "uart_remove_one_port" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
uart_remove_one_port \- detach a driver defined port structure
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" uart_remove_one_port
.BI "(struct uart_driver *drv "  ","
.BI "struct uart_port *uport "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "drv" 12
pointer to the uart low level driver structure for this port
.IP "uport" 12
uart port structure for this port
.SH "CONTEXT"
task context, might sleep
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This unhooks (and hangs up) the specified port structure from the
core driver.  No further calls will be made to the low-level code
for this port.
